x4freetext: Neutrons were detected in a 12.7cm diameter*2.54
cm thick Nuclear Enterprise NE213 liquid scintillator
optically coupled to a RTC58AVP photomultiplier.
A small NE111 plastic scintillator coupled to an
RCA8575 phototube was mounted near the target at 90
degr. to the beam direction, as a monitor of target
The 12C targets consisted of self-supporting films of
polystyrene. The target thickness and uniformity were
determined by measuring the energy loss of 241Am
The uncertainties associated with the differential
b)The number of target nuclei per cm**2 contributes
c)The number of incident particles per total charge
d)Errors in solid angle are less than 1%.
e)The neutron detection efficiency contributes about
The totality of the uncertainties from these various
parameters results in an overall uncertainty of 9.5-
11.5% for the differential cross sections at Ed=7.0MeV
and 9.1 MeV, and of 15-20% for those at Ed=13.0 MeV and
for the excitation function at an angle of 25 degr.lab.
